the london festival ballet opened for two weeks 
at the metropolitan opera house with sir frederick ashtons romeo 
and juliet and the evening was a triumph for peter schaufuss as 
romeo 
schaufuss at 40 looked youthful and singlemindedly ardent 
about juliet danced tuesday by 20yearold susan hogard a native 
of australia voted best newcomer by a dance magazine two years 
ago miss hogard is very good but her juliet stopped short of being 
incandescent 
miss hogard seemed more comfortable with the later part of the 
ballet when juliet is making more mature decisions about how to 
keep from marrying paris than in the beginning when the character 
is more girlish 
schaufuss has been the companys artistic director since 1984 
one of his first moves was to talk sir frederick into helping stage 
his romeo for this company sir frederick choreographed it to 
prokofievs music in 1955 for the royal danish ballet where 
schaufuss mother mona vangsaa was the original juliet and his 
father frank schaufuss was the original mercutio the company 
dropped the ballet in 1965 and schaufuss didnt want it to be lost 
it is more spare in numbers of dancers scenery and general 
ambiance than sir kenneth macmillans 1965 romeo and juliet 
for the british royal ballet 
nielsbjorn larsen the original tybalt helped stage this 
production on tuesday frank schaufuss was the prince of verona 
who tries to keep the peace the wellknown british dancers 
alexander grant and lynn seymour were lord and lady capulet graham 
bond conducted the evening which was dedicated to the memory of 
sir frederick 
one high point of the opening night performance was the trio 
showing happiness and friendship of romeo mercutio maximiliano 
guerra and benvolio matz skoog guerra a native of argentina 
who won a gold medal at the varna international ballet competition 
last year was a charming fleet lighthearted mercutio 
his opposite the heavyhanded arrogant tybalt was danced with 
aplomb by londonborn nicholas johnson a company member since 1975 
the london festival ballet changed its name to the english 
national ballet on june 1 but appeared last week in washington and 
now in new york under the old name its last american tour was 11 
years ago 
