higher limit had a 30 percent increase in fatalities twice the 
increase recorded by the institute and the transportation 
department for 1987 
brian oneill president of the research institute which is 
financed by insurance companies said states that kept the maximum 
speed limit at 55 mph had no significant increase in road deaths 
