and the united states recognized eric arturo delvalle as the 
countrys legitimate president and gave him control over frozen 
panamanian funds in us banks 
in june 1988 the administration sought to escalate the 
sanctions by barring payments by us firms to the noriega 
government tax and traderelated payments were to be diverted 
instead to a federal reserve bank escrow account 
