<TEXT>
nissan did about everything right on its new fourthgeneration 
z car except for the name 
something more reflective of the car being a real magnet for 
young men might be appropriate and im only counting the youthful 
males who turned all the way around in their car seats or pulled 
alongside my test car and spent minutes taking in every inch of 
this auto 
there also was the fellow who evidently buoyed by the sheer 
sight of the 300zx cheered and raised a clenched fist in 
admiration believe me none of these guys was looking at me 
ask nissan if young males are the buyers of the 1990 300zx and 
theyll talk about psychographics the mental makeup of buyers 
not just demographics such as age sex and household income and 
theyll say women are likely buyers too 
the buyers are auto enthusiasts who want to be noticed said 
nissan spokesman ec mueller they have upper education and 
income theyre professionals wanting to make a statement 
judging from the reaction the bright red test car got there are 
plenty of people who want to make a statement on todays roads the 
question for them is do you have the 27000plus for the 300zx 
make no mistake the car is well done its lower and wider than 
its predecessor but has a longer wheelbase its 3liter v6 
produces 222 horsepower and is smooth and powerful getting the car 
up to 60 miles per hour in under seven seconds theres an even 
faster model a twinturbo 300zx due out this fall that brings 
even more horsepower 300 
the tbar roof is there offering the easy option of hardtop or 
open roof 
the optional nissan bose sound system was exceptional 
and the real beauty of the 300zx was the suspension it retains 
the roadhugging characteristics of a fine sports coupe yet it 
doesnt jostle riders harshly as many other sports cars do its a 
fine blend a good compromise between comfort and performance 
as nissan spokesman mueller put it on a six or sevenhour 
drive you dont regret being in the 300zx 
still making statements on the road isnt cheap like all 
upscale sports cars the 300zx is pricey and insurance costs will 
be pricey too 
this is the fourth major design of the nissan z car its also 
the companys response to critics who in recent years said nissan 
had lost sight of the original z car image that of a fine sports 
coupe in fact the first z the 1970 240z that was priced at 
3526 was motor trend magazines car of the year 
over the years nearly 1 million z cars have been sold as the 
car evolved and its name changed as larger engines were added in 
1974 it was renamed the 260z because of the addition of the 
26liter engine then 280z in 1975 280zx in 1979 and 300zx in 
the 1984 model year 
sales of the z car peaked at 73101 in calendar 1984 the year 
the third generation z car debuted then declined each year to just 
19357 in 1988 nissan attributes some of the decrease to people 
waiting until this year for the newly designed z 
it comes in two body styles a twoseater that was the test car 
and a twoplustwo version both have rakish sleek exteriors and 
firm formfitting front seats 
drivers must be ready to drive with their side mirrors as the 
rear hatch lid is so sloping that the rear window is somewhat 
small the lines from the rear window defroster add some 
distortion also the side window pillars are thick and large and 
make it difficult to see to the right and back 
inside the twoseater was a small indented shelf area in the 
midsection behind the seats for storage tall items fit well there 
but also obstructed the rear view 
smaller items fit all the way back where clearance was least 
the back also had cloth cases for storage of the two troof window 
parts and straps to buckle them in so they dont slide around 
the instrument panel had large easytoread numbers and letters 
no digital gadgets here but beware of that speedometer that goes 
to 160 mph nissan decided it could be dangerous to have a car that 
might surpass a drivers ability so theres a fuel cutoff at 148 
mph no burying the speedometer on this car 
a nice touch was having all the adjustment buttons for the 
cruise control embedded in the steering wheel the cruise couldnt 
be activated however until a main switch on the dashboard to the 
left of the steering wheel was turned on 
nissan said competitors include the toyota supra which starts 
at more than 22000 and the chevrolet corvette which starts at 
more than 31000 over the years fewer z car owners are reporting 
trouble according to consumer reports magazine the periodical 
ranked the 1984 and 1985 300zx cars as average followed by better 
than average for the 1986 model and much better than average for 
the 1987 model 
</TEXT>
