<TEXT>
smacking on a wad of bubblegum 
12yearold kiva henderson chats excitedly about the boys and girls 
club of annapolis bywater which operates practically at the front 
door of her home they help you with your homework here it 
helped to bring up my grades she says 
elevenyearold keith collins chimes in i like it because 
its a good way to stay off the streets we cant get into trouble 
here 
while the nonprofit boys clubs of america has some 1100 
affiliates nationwide the annapolis club is one of 76 now located 
in public housing projects in an effort to keep disadvantaged kids 
from using drugs or dropping out 
the organization hopes to expand that effort over the next five 
years to reach an additional 700000 disadvantaged children through 
300 more such strategically located clubs 
the clubs organize sports trips and other activities to build 
youngsters confidence and teach good work habits teamwork 
honesty and selfreliance 
robbie callaway the organizations government liaison says the 
first boys club at a public housing project was established in east 
st louis ill in 1953 but he said the national office 
reenergized its efforts 3 years ago because of concerns about 
increasing drug abuse and crime by youngsters 
public housing was identified as the greatest need because no 
one else was doing anything there he says 
samuel r pierce jr housing and urban development secretary 
under president reagan lent his name and influence to the effort 
but no government money was forthcoming from hud which is now 
under investigation for doling out millions of dollars to projects 
backed by prominent republicans during pierces tenure 
still callaway said pierces public statements of support 
caused the organization to be swamped with requests that led to 
the opening of 23 public housing clubs in 1987 and 1988 
now boys club officials are looking to new hud secretary jack 
kemp to make a financial commitment 
speaking at an april 10 press briefing at the white house kemp 
a former boys club member and later pro football player said 
i dont know if there are subsidies for football fields but if 
i can find public monies in hud to support the boys clubs and girls 
clubs of america going into these public housing projects and 
setting up athletic teams im convinced that that would have a 
significant impact upon putting an end to this scourge of drug 
trafficking 
to bolster claims of decreased crime with boys clubs programs 
officials point to preliminary findings of a threeyear study of 
clubs in albany and binghamton ny jacksonville fla peoria 
and rockford ill meridian miss houston and brownsville 
texas and martinez upland and san jose calif 
the reports evaluators from columbia university and the 
american health foundation said substance abuse problems and 
juvenile delinquency have decreased in frequency and in severity 
within housing projects served by a boys and girls club 
other evidence is anecdotal 
