pepsico inc said wednesday its secondquarter 
earnings climbed 206 percent as its soft drink snack foods and 
restaurant divisions each contributed doubledigit gains in revenue 
and operating profits 
we have tremendous momentum in all three of our businesses 
said d wayne calloway chairman and chief executive 
the puchase nybased company said it earned 2649 million 
or 1 a share in the three months ended june 17 compared with 
2196 million or 84 cents a share a year earlier 
secondquarter revenue rose 238 percent to 359 billion from 
29 billion a year earlier 
the latest results included an aftertax credit of 15 million 
for several onetime events the largest of which was a decision to 
keep rather than sell a foreign bottling operation 
the operating profit from the companys soft drink business 
soared 60 percent to 2396 million while sales rose 33 percent to 
15 billion 
excluding onetime events and the net effect of bottling 
acquisitions operating profits still rose 32 percent and sales 
rose 9 percent 
the growth in operating profits reflected strong domestic 
results due to volume growth higher pricing and efforts to 
control costs the company said 
it said its diet pepsi and mountain dew brands posted 
doubledigit growth in case sales in the united states 
the snack foods business had an operating profit of 1917 
million up 24 percent from a year earlier on a 17 percent revenue 
increase to 958 million its domestic profits rose at a 
doubledigit pace while international profits more than tripled 
the company said domestic volume for fritolay rose 8 percent 
led by gains in the ruffles fritos and doritos brands 
the companys restaurant business earnings rose 15 percent to 
1021 million while sales rose 20 percent to nearly 12 billion 
earnings were up 41 percent to 518 million at the pizza hut 
restaurants and 60 percent to 324 million at taco bell 
restuarants but fell 44 percent to 179 million at kentucky fried 
chicken 
the decline at kentucky fried chicken was blamed on an 8 
